On 24 July 2020, Israeli police forces forcefully dispersed a protest against the Prime Minister, claiming that the protest was taking to long, arresting 55 protesters, the protest was held in front of the PM's house, in Jerusalem. The protest was part of the 'Black Flag Movement' [size=around 4000]

On 23 July 2020, hundreds of Haredi Jewish, and anti Zionist, citizens of Israel demonstrated against the imprisonment 3 months ago of a demonstrator from the community for allegedly attacking a policeman, in Jerusalem-Mea Shearim. The demonstrators clashed with police forces [size=hundreds]

On 21 July 2020, thousands of Israelis demonstrated in front of the PM's house, in Jerusalem, against the government. The demonstration turned violent after demonstrators clashed with police forces, as a result 34 demonstrators were arrested. [size=thousands]

notes: On 21 July 2020, Arab and Jewish restaurant owners protested in Haifa, against the government's plan to close down restaurants, due to a rise in coronavirus cases. [size=no report]

On 19 July 2020, social workers protested in Beersheba city, against their poor working conditions and demanded an increase in pay. [size=no report]

On 19 July 2020, around 200 Arab Israeli citizens of Israel clashed with Israeli police forces, during a demonstration against the demolition of an Islamic cemetery in Jaffa, the police fired tear gas to disperse the rioters. [size=around 200]

Property destruction: On 19 July 2020, Israeli military forces intercepted and shot down a drone that entered Israeli air space from Lebanon, the Israeli forces claimed the drone was monitoring troops movement along the border.
